Another existing approach is to directly solve a matrix-form problem in (12) by modifying conventional CS algorithms such as orthogonal matching pursuit (OMP) [32, 33].
This approach, however, still requires significant computational complexity that comes from large-scale matrix multiplications.
For example, Table I in Sec. VI shows that the OMP algorithm to solve the matrix-form problem in (12) requires the complexity order of 4×10154superscript10154\times 10^{15} in our simulation with B=10𝐵10B=10, R=5𝑅5R=5, and S/N=0.04𝑆𝑁0.04S/N=0.04.
To overcome the limitations of the existing CS approaches, in the following section, we will present a new low-complexity approach to solve the CS recovery problem in (12).
